description: Our hero Dan Morgenstern speaks fondly of the great pianist, singer, and composer Jimmy Rowles -- as an accompanist and soloist, beginning in 1941, with side-glances at Stan Getz and Carol Sloane -- in this interview at his home last year.  Recorded by Michael Steinman for JAZZ LIVES (http://www.jazzlives.wordpress.com).
